18/01/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- The defence ministry announced on Monday (January 17th) it will send a new contingent of commandos to Afghanistan as part of peacekeeping operation in Herat province. The 222 commandos will spend six months under Italian command. Currently, there are four Albanian contingents in Afghanistan. In 2010, 554 soldiers served in the mission. (Klan, Alsat, Vizion +, Top News - 17/01/11)
